        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer849953844" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer339827673771703956"> A relatively quick read but packs a punch about the effects of exploration in South America and its material and emotional costs to the natural and human world. Much like Things Fall Apart, this novel takes on the politics of colonialism, the intrusion of Western values on indigenous/tribal ways of life, and the costs of misreading. The Old Man is a strong-minded, likeable character who attempts to navigate different worlds he belongs to. His insights about the natural world and non-human anima</span>
  <span id="freeText339827673771703956" style="display:none"> A relatively quick read but packs a punch about the effects of exploration in South America and its material and emotional costs to the natural and human world. Much like Things Fall Apart, this novel takes on the politics of colonialism, the intrusion of Western values on indigenous/tribal ways of life, and the costs of misreading. The Old Man is a strong-minded, likeable character who attempts to navigate different worlds he belongs to. His insights about the natural world and non-human animals' intelligence are significant to this tall-tale about the demise of arrogant greedy men who attempt to dominate and defy nature and the power of imaginative writing to heal and soothe trauma. And let's not forget the cat! She is a frightening and powerful figure, acting as a protector of the jungle and traditional ways of life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="339827673771703956" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
