<div id="review_3210225084" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3210225084" />
    <a title="leni_hermanni" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44811987-leni-hermanni"><img alt="leni_hermanni" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1597748877p2/44811987.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3210225084?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="leni_hermanni" class="user" itemprop="url" name="leni_hermanni" href="/user/show/44811987-leni-hermanni">leni_hermanni</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789607073150" href="/book/show/12263497">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3210225084" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16385254243307625752">This must be one of the most moving and captivating books I&apos;ve ever read. The description of the exotic Amazon sceneries are exquisite. My favourite thing, though, is that the author portrays civilised humans as idiotic barbarians spoiling the untouched natural habitat of several magnificent species of animals and you can&apos;t help but sympathize with the animals after the monstrosities mentioned. Once I get to a couple more of his works I&apos;m sure Sepulveda will have already gained a place among my </span>
  <span id="freeText16385254243307625752" style="display:none">This must be one of the most moving and captivating books I've ever read. The description of the exotic Amazon sceneries are exquisite. My favourite thing, though, is that the author portrays civilised humans as idiotic barbarians spoiling the untouched natural habitat of several magnificent species of animals and you can't help but sympathize with the animals after the monstrosities mentioned. Once I get to a couple more of his works I'm sure Sepulveda will have already gained a place among my favourites!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16385254243307625752" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


